==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mouflon
<hw>Mouf"lon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>mouflon</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A wild sheep
(<spn>Ovis musimon</spn>), inhabiting the mountains of Sardinia,
Corsica, etc. Its horns are very large, with a triangular base and
rounded angles. It is supposed by some to be the original of the
domestic sheep. Called also <altname>musimon</altname> or
<altname>musmon</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>moufflon</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mought</ent>⟦br⟧
